Mark the divided flock of Christ. Ο wretched party strife, but what have I to do with this? Mark how many dangers by sea and land you have lived through; when France beheld you. when Tagus led you in your youth to the west. O happy in your lotl the main subsides, and the winds at command come to fill your sails. Let Edinburgh carry off the palm, through her vantage as capital; believe me, in love of the king she will never conquer her sisters.
